title: No major issues found with Artemis 1 mission
summary: An ongoing review of data from the Artemis 1 mission has turned up no issues that would delay the crewed Artemis 2 mission scheduled for launch late next year.

title: BREAKING! USSF Allocates Launch Complexes To 4 Commercial Launchers
summary: The US Space Force and Space Launch Delta 45 have awarded 3 Cape Canaveral Space Force Station launch complexes to commercial space launch providers ushering in a new era of launches from Cape Canaveral Space Force Station in Florida.

title: EXCLUSIVE! Inspired 24 Launches Mission To Democratize Access To Space
summary: Introducing The Inspired 24, a group of space enthusiasts dedicated to promoting the democratization of space!

title: BREAKING! NASA Targeting November 2024 For Artemis II Launch
summary: Along with announcing a target date for Artemis II, NASA also gave many other updates on the Artemis programme.

title: Rocket Lab ‘very happy’ with Space Force plan to procure launch services
summary: Rocket Lab’s chief executive Peter Beck says the company played an active role in reshaping the U.S. government’s approach to buying launch services.
